  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The Core Spotlight APIs help you provide a comprehensive description of an item and to add it to the on-device index. They support indexing items at any time, such as when your app loads."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To start indexing app content, perform these steps:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitemattributeset"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object and specify properties that describe the item you want to index."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitem"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object to represent the item. A "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitem"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object has a unique identifier that lets you refer to it later."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If needed, specify a domain identifier so that you can gather multiple items together and manage them as a group."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Associate the attribute set with the searchable item."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Add the searchable item to the index."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As you use Core Spotlight to make your app content searchable, you can also use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsuseractivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to make app states and navigation points searchable and to help users return to an activity or app location when they tap on a search result. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Both Core Spotlight and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsuseractivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " use a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitemattributeset"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to describe a searchable item, provide rich metadata that is displayed in search results, and prevent duplication of items in search results. Unlike the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsuseractivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " API, however, Core Spotlight APIs don’t require users to visit the content before it gets indexed. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you use both APIs, you can improve the ranking of your items in search results and prevent item duplication by specifying the same value in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitemattributeset/1621569-relateduniqueidentifier"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsuseractivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitem/1621672-uniqueidentifier"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corespotlight/cssearchableitem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ")."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If your app has related content on a website, you should also mark up your website and support universal links to ensure that users can open your native app when they tap a search result supplied by your website (if your app isn’t installed, tapping the result opens Safari). "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
